---
description: Use when generating or updating documentation (keywords: docs, documentation, architecture, design, explanation)
---

When generating documentation:

- prefer short, well-structured sections
- include examples when they improve clarity
- mention responsibilities, boundaries, and key flows
- avoid vague wording and generic statements
- write for engineers who are new to the project
- reuse existing terminology from the repo when possible
- prefer updating existing docs over creating duplicates
